  "text": "The exact solutions corresponding to the KI phantom of R = 0.9 cm were calculated as follows. The upper limit of n (i.e., N), was taken to be 100. Using the X-ray source and LAC spectra in Fig. 2a , values for μ n (0) were calculated via Equation (A9) for n = 1 to 100. These values were subsequently converted to ν n using Equation (11), and C n was calculated by Equation [CITATION_1] . Finally, F n was determined by Equation (5) to obtain the cupping profile, f (r).",
